<br>
In the interest of contributing to constructive suggestions, I have the following ideas.<br>
<br>
1.  Entirely remove all lore, magic,and no drop items everywhere, and while you're at it remove all spell casting, thereby contributing to the most realistic world ever yet available.  What happens when you attack a dragon?  You die.  Everyone dies.  That's because dragons are big and we aren't.<br>
<br>
2.  Go directly to a consent based combat system similar to Mu*s.  If you think you deserve to kill a monster, you command it secretly to die and it does.  This would make for great role-playing opportunities, and allow for acts of heroism unheard of on other worlds.<br>
<br>
3. Recycle the coding that allowed people to play monsters, then make that all they could play.  Harvest the character information from every account with a character in Firiona Vie and send them out to kill the monsters.  That would....  Hmm.  It would prevent farming for sure!<br>
<br>
4.  Sell the world code for EQ and let every geek and addict in the world with far too much time host Norrath on their own servers.  Everyone could have exactly the world they wanted.  Well, everyone with a T3 line at least.<br>
<br>
5.  Alter Ankles' character profile permenently so it never again looks like she's wearing pants.  That would contribute immensely to RP.<br>
<br>
6.  Add a creature to the game that is small and blue and has an annoyed high-pitched voice that shows up and mocks any character that kills the same monster too often.  It would also follow around anyone selling farmed items, and would be summoned automatically to the location of any dood who is abusing his numberpad priviledges.  This coding could be modeled after the paperclip guy from Mircosoft Word.<br>
<br>
7. Turn complete control of Verant over to Rudolph Giuliani.  We know he's out of work, and we know he can deal with anything no matter how fucked it is.<br>
<br>
Hope that helps.<br>
<br>
Val<br>
